parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake light comes on
the brakes make a grinding or crunching noise
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the vehicle vibrates or shakes when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An inaccurate fuel gauge can cause the vehicle to run out of fuel, leading to unexpected stalls, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge shows incorrect readings
the vehicle stalls or runs out of fuel

the fuel level does not match the actual amount of fuel in the tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of available repair parts can cause delays in fixing the fuel gauge issue, leaving the driver at risk of experiencing unexpected stalls or running out of fuel.

the repair is delayed
the driver is left without a solution.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the suspension and steering system can cause the vehicle to become unstable, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or wobbles violently when hitting potholes or driving at certain speeds

the vehicle sways from side to side

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle and rim can cause loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stabilizer bar can cause the vehicle to shake or wobble abnormally, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or wobbles abnormally when driving at speeds of at least 30 mph.
